headline.main: HOWARD CARTER, 66, EGYPTOLOGIST, DIES; Discoverer and Excavator of Tut-ankh-Amen's Tomb Had Made Other Noted Finds BEGAN EXPLORING IN 1890 Pupil and Aide of Flinders Petrie--Revived Interest in Ancient Civilizations

snippet: LONDON, March 3.--Howard Carter, Egyptologist who earned world fame for his discovery and exploration, in association with the fifth Earl of Carnarvon, of the tomb of Tut-ankh-Amen, died in his London home todey at the age of 66.

byline.original: Wireless to THE NEW YORK TIMES
